Done. Here's what was delivered:

- **`drizzle/0003_product_images_bucket.sql`** — creates the `product-images` Storage bucket (`public: true`) and idempotent RLS policies: public SELECT, service_role-only INSERT/UPDATE
- **`lib/storage/upload-product-image.ts`** — `uploadProductImage(supabase, slug, data, contentType)` uploads to the bucket and returns the public URL; handles content-type → extension mapping including `image/svg+xml → .svg`
- **`lib/storage/upload-product-image.test.ts`** — 6 tests covering bucket name, path/extension mapping, public URL return, and error throwing
- **`scripts/fixtures/images/*.svg`** — placeholder SVGs for each of the 3 seed products
- **`scripts/seed-products.ts`** — `seedProducts(db, supabase?)` now accepts an optional Supabase client; when provided, reads fixture SVGs, uploads them, and stores the public URLs; falls back gracefully if upload fails

All 77 tests green, lint clean, typecheck clean.

